1. Libya has had only one king in its lifetime; the first and last monarch of Libya was known 
as King Idris I.
2. Libya is home to the largest proven oil reserves in Africa. 
3. Historically, Libya was divided into only three regionals namely Fezzan, Tripolitania, 
and Cyrenaica
4.The highest mountain in Libya is Bette Peak at around 7,434 feet tall.
5. Cyrene, present-day Shahhat, is a city in Libya that was part of the Greek empire that 
existed hundreds of years ago. It was one of the most important Greek cities as it was the 
center of philosophy education.
